Code-Level Root Cause Analysis
The Smoking Gun — confirmPasscode() method, line ~320

// If phone is not verified on file, return fail response.
String reason = remoteSupportService.checkPhoneVerified(
    person, personVo, rpEvent, refOtpSupplier, 
    RemoteSupportServiceImpl.CONFIRM_PASSCODE, origin
);


This call to checkPhoneVerified() is the root cause. Here’s exactly why:

The Failure Chain

VerifyPhone  → hits BC4 → writes phone verification data to DB
                          → creates RpPhoneVerification record
                          → updates PersonProofingStatus → OTP_sent
                          → updates RpEvent with OTP supplier

ConfirmPasscode → hits BC5 (round-robin)
                → calls checkPhoneVerified()
                → queries DB for phone verification state
                → FINDS NOTHING or STALE DATA ← BUG IS HERE
                → returns "Phone was not verified for customer"


Why the DB Query Fails on BC5
Look at how confirmPasscode() sets up its context before calling checkPhoneVerified():

// In confirmPasscode():
long otpSupplierId = RefOtpSupplier.LEXISNEXIS_RDP_OTP_SUPPLIER_ID;  // ← HARDCODED
RefOtpSupplier refOtpSupplier = refOtpSupplierDataService.findBySupplierId(otpSupplierId);

RpEvent rpEvent = rpEventDataService.findLatestEventByPersonId(personId);

RpPhoneVerification rpPhoneVerification = 
    rpPhoneVerificationService.findPhoneVerificationByEventId(rpEvent.getEventId());

if (rpPhoneVerification != null) {
    personVo.setMobileNumber(rpPhoneVerification.getMobilePhoneNumber());
}

personVo.setTransactionKeyHasExpired(rpEvent.transactionKeyHasExpired());


Notice what’s NOT set on personVo before checkPhoneVerified() is called:
	∙	No phoneVerified flag
	∙	No OTP status
	∙	No passcode sent confirmation
The checkPhoneVerified() method (in RemoteSupportService) almost certainly reads phone verification state from either PersonProofingStatus or RpPhoneVerification, and the timing/transaction issue means BC5 sees a different DB state than BC4 just wrote.

The Transaction Timing Problem

// verifyPhone() on BC4:
phoneVerificationService.sendPasscodeSuccessful(personVo, refOtpSupplier);
// ↑ This writes to DB inside its own @Transactional boundary

person = personDataService.findByPK(personVo.getId());
PersonProofingStatus latestProofingStatus = 
    personProofingStatusService.getByPersonId(personId);
boolean otpSent = latestProofingStatus != null && 
    latestProofingStatus.getRefRpStatus().getStatusCode() 
