The class is annotated @Transactional at the class level:

@Service("remoteProofingService")
@Transactional          // ← entire class is transactional
public class RemoteProofingServiceImpl implements Serializable, RemoteProofingService {


This means verifyPhone() and confirmPasscode() each run in their own transaction. The commit from verifyPhone() on BC4 may not be fully visible to BC5 depending on DB isolation level and connection pool timing — especially when the calls come in rapid succession (which the calling app does).

